Luke A. McGuinness

Bio

I am data scientist and enthusiastic R user/developer. I maintain several research-orientated open-source R packages including robvis and medrxivr, in addition to some smaller utility/learning packages (e.g. wordcountaddin and pathformatr).

Outside of my work, I am an avid fan of running, LEGO and really terrible movies.

 

Education

PhD in Epidemiology/Population Health Sciences | Bristol Medical School, Bristol, UK | Jan 2019 - Mar 2021

MSc in Epidemiology | London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine, London, UK | Sept 2016 - Sept 2017

BA (Mod.) in Genetics | Trinity College Dublin, Dublin, Ireland | Sept 2012 - May 2016
